          "",
          "Logan Boese"
        ],
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "In life, you were a teacher. A molder of young minds, happy in your career choice and moreover with your growing family. You had a spouse and a child, (one who had just barely missed being taught by you, and who was very grateful to have avoided that,) and a promising future. Late one afternoon, you were coming back from a grocery run when your vehicle was struck by a drunk driver. After the horrific accident, all you knew was that your child was hurt. Badly. You could hear them cry and scream, begging for your help. You yourself lost consciousness before they did, the sound of their screams the last thing you heard as the darkness mercifully claimed you and ended your too-weak struggles to help them. When you awoke, you were told that they had slipped into a coma and died of their injuries. You also found that the drunk driver, the son of a rich and powerful politician, had gotten off more or less scott free. You vowed then and there that this would not stand. You dedicated yourself whole heartedly to their destruction. Legal routes failed you, they were stymied at every attempt as they were backed by Old money. It didn't matter. You abandoned your job and all but abandoned your spouse as you searched for any and all means to bring them down. Your research turned up very little on it's own. Until, that is, you got an email. It didn't say much, but contained a video clip and several scattered articles that painted a disturbing picture. The implications were too much for you, save for one. There was power in this world beyond legal, and all you had to do was Find it, and Take it. You started piecing things together, made preparations, started training yourself for what was to come, and started searching the city for the new predator you had been told lurked there. You found one, tracked it, and \"convinced\" it to gift you this power. Your quarry did not survive until morning. After that, you were listless, your vengeance was had and your old life was more or less gone. You even still lived in your former basement, (Although your spouse thought you dead.) Until, that was, that you were approached by another of your kind. They didn't tell you their name, but they did tell you how to survive in this new world of yours. The dos, and the donts, and the ins and the outs of the society of \"Kindred.\" They also told you where, and when you had to go to get yourself Recognized, and, perhaps most importantly, what would happen if you went against the rules of Kindred society. Then, they disappeared."
        ],
